<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslims, Croats Coordinate Federation Law </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslims, Croats Coordinate Federation Law </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2704181994 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1700 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2704181994 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At a meeting in Split, groups of experts of the 
governments of the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna and 
Bosnia-Herzegovina have coordinated a draft law on the 
government of the federation of Bosnia-Herzegovina and a law on 
the federation ministries. The future government of the 
federation of Bosnia-Herzegovina is to have 12 ministries, at 
least five of which will be headed by representatives of the 
Croat nation. In addition, two ministers will be without 
portfolio -- the government will have 15 members, prime minister 
included, it is laid down in the draft law on the government of 
the federation of Bosnia-Herzegovina. Zaran Buntic, the 
chairman of the Judicial Council [Sudbeno Vijece] of the Croat 
republic of Herceg-Bosna, said that the second round of expert 
negotiations on the draft laws on the official gazette of the 
federation and on the stamp of the federation would be held 
soon. The draft law on the delineation of cantons is also being 
prepared. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

