<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Fierce' Inter-Muslim Fighting Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Fierce' Inter-Muslim Fighting Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2604131794 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1220 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2604131794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Petrovac, April 26 (TANJUG) -- Local Moslem media 
report fierce inter-Moslem clashes in Western Bosnia over the 
past 24 hours. The heaviest battles between supporters of 
moderate western Bosnia leader Fikret Abdic and troops of 
radical Bosnian Moslem leader Alija Izetbegovic are being fought 
in the areas of Varoska Rijeka and Buzim. Both sides are firing 
from small arms, anti- aircraft guns, machine-guns, mortars and 
grenade launchers. Each side claims to have inflicted heavy 
casualties on the other side and to have taken prisoners, but 
the front line has remained intact. 
  The two sides recently exchanged prisoners in the presence 
of 
U.N. and Red Cross officials. Abdic's supporters released 280 
prisoners in exchange for 75 prisoners held by the other side. 
The prisoners released from Bihac by Izetbegovic's troops say 
they were starved and maltreated, while those held in Abdic's 
stronghold of Velika Kladusa did not have any complaints. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

