<H3> <TI>   Gligorov Comments on Language Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gligorov Comments on Language Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2704155194 Skopje MIC in English 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2704155194 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MIC </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Gligorov: The Language Problem -- An </F>
Internal Question"] 
  [Text] "It is not our issue, it is their internal 
question," President Gligorov stated last night at the Skopje 
airport, upon his return from the two day official visit to 
Bulgaria, in his retrospective on the problem with the failure 
to sign any agreements because of the disputed formulation 
"Macedonian language." 
  "The Bulgarian Government made several remarks that will 
have 
to be reviewed by both sides, however, the problem is the 
formulation of the Macedonian language," said Gligorov. 
  "Our stance is clear -- the Macedonian language cannot be 
controversial and it is not up for negotiations. These are two 
completely different languages and I think that we will make 
some progress in further talks." 
  Gligorov feels that President Zhelev has an understanding 
for 
this matter, it is simply a reality that has to be accepted like 
any other reality. 

</TEXT>

