<H3> <TI>   Country Charges Duties on Slovene Imports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Country Charges Duties on Slovene Imports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94P20662A Ljubljana SLOVENIA WEEKLY in English 20-26 Mar 94 
p 7 </F>

<F P=103> 94P20662A </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana SLOVENIA WEEKLY </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "New Macedonian Duties on Slovene </F>
Imports"] 
  [Text] Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia 
-- FYROM] this week began charging two duties totaling 15 
percent on the bulk of Slovene imports: a 7.5-percent levy and a 
7.5-percent special duty designed to spread the tax burden. 
  The new duties apply to all classes of goods that make up 
Slovenia's most significant exports to Macedonia: 
  -- furniture and other wooden products, 
  -- poultry, 
  -- paper and cardboard, 
  -- tires, 
  -- washing powders, 
  -- cosmetics, 
  -- household appliances. 
  This effectively means that the bilateral free trade 
agreement signed in 1992 is no longer in force. 

</TEXT>

