<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslim Attack Before UNPROFOR's `Very Eyes' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslim Attack Before UNPROFOR's `Very Eyes' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2704200394 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1922 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2704200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Bratunac, April 27 (TANJUG) -- Moslems on Wednesday 
opened fire from anti-aircraft machineguns, infantry weapons and 
snipers on Serb parts of Sarajevo before the very eyes of the 
United Nations Protection Force (UNPROFOR), the Bosnian Serb 
Army said in a statement. The targets of artillery and infantry 
fire on Wednesday were also Serb villages and Army positions in 
the areas of Konjic south of Sarajevo, Srbobran (formerly Donji 
Vakuf), Olovo and Kladanj in central Bosnia, Orasje, Doboj, 
Gradacac, Brcko, Teslic and Mount Vlasic in northern Bosnia, 
Mount Majevica in north-eastern Bosnia and Bihac in western 
Bosnia, the statement said. 
  The Bosnian Serb Army on Wednesday neutralized a Moslem 
terrorist group in the area of Bihac, it added. Moslem attacks 
on the almost entire territory of the Serb Republic in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina continues at a time when the Serb side is 
proposing a general ceasefire in the war-ravaged former Yugoslav 
Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina, the statement said. 
  In the night between Tuesday and Wednesday, the Serb and 
Moslem sides exchanged prisoners, civilians and the bodies of 
killed fighters in the vicinity of Bihac. The exchange was 
carried out on an "all-for-all" principle and in the presence of 
UNPROFOR monitors, the Bosnian Serb Army said. The Moslem side 
handed over four prisoners, 12 civilians and six bodies of 
killed soldiers and the Serb side four prisoners, nine civilians 
and eight bodies of killed fighters, the statement said. 

</TEXT>

