<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croatia Reportedly Preparing Attack in North </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Croatia Reportedly Preparing Attack in North </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904101794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0836 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2904101794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Banja Luka, 29 Apr (TANJUG) -- The Republic of 
Croatia is by all accounts intensively preparing for an imminent 
attack on the Serb positions in Posavina, the press center of 
the republic of Srpska army's First Krajina Corps said in a 
statement today, citing well-informed sources. Croatia's army 
has recently accumulated units and military equipment in 
Posavina, on the left bank of the River Sava, mainly in the 
wider areas of Slavonski Brod and Zupanja. According to the 
same source, large numbers of Croats and Muslims from Posavina 
are members of these units, and some new units have also been 
founded. [passage omitted] 
  The press center notes that Croatian media have recently 
carried an increasing number of "reports" about the Serbian 
side's preparations for attacks against the Croatian positions 
in Posavina. This is a typical form of media preparations: an 
attempt to condemn the Serbian side in advance before strong 
Croatian-Muslim attacks begin. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

