<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Swedish UN Soldier Injured in Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Swedish UN Soldier Injured in Sarajevo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2904110594 Paris AFP in English 1037 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2904110594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Stockholm, April 29 (AFP) -- A Swedish UN soldier 
was injured Thursday [28 April] in Sarajevo when he stepped on a 
land mine near Mount Igman while on patrol duty, the Defence 
Ministry said Friday [29 April]. 21 year-old Kristoffer 
Melinder, of Sweden's Ninth Company, suffered a fracture and 
splinters to a leg and was taken to a French hospital for 
surgery. The 9th Company, part of the joint Nordic peacekeeping 
force, is currently in Sarajevo to supervise the ceasefire. In 
total, there are over 880 Swedes in the Nordic battalion. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

