<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Continuing Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on Continuing Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Miners Extend Ultimatum Deadline </H4>

<F P=102> LD2804222894 Warsaw PAP in Polish 2134 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2804222894 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, Konin, 28 Apr--After 15 hours, at 2310 
today, talks between Industry and Trade Minister Marek Pol and 
the striking brown coal miners were recessed until Friday at 
0600. 
  The trade unionists have decided to extend the deadline of 
the ultimatum they have given the government to present a 
schedule of actions that will implement the demands put forward 
by branch trade unions and Solidarity. 

</TEXT>

