<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Continuing Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on Continuing Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Talks With Brown Coal Miners Break Down </H4>

<F P=102> LD2904081794 Warsaw PAP in Polish 0509 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2904081794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Konin, 29 Apr--Talks in Konin between Industry and 
Trade Minister Marek Pol and representatives of the striking 
brown coal miners did not resume at 0600 on 29 April as 
announced. According to unofficial reports, the trade unionists 
think that the government broke off Thursday's negotiations. 
  On 28 April, during negotiations lasting approximately 12 
hours, the trade unionists decided to extend the deadline set 
for the government to present a timetable for the implementation 
of mining and Solidarity demands until 1400 on Friday. 

</TEXT>

