<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Continuing Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on Continuing Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Supplies to Power Stations Suspended </H4>

<F P=102> LD2904082394 Warsaw PAP in Polish 0543 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2904082394 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Konin, 29 Apr--On 29 April, Zdzislaw Stasiak, 
spokesman for the National Strike Committee of the Brown Coal 
Miners, told listeners of local radio station "66" in Konin that 
at 0620 the committee decided to suspend coal supplies to 
Belchatow, Konin, Patnow, and Adamow power stations. The 
spokesman explained that this was the result of prolonged 
negotiations with the government. According to Stasiak, the 
suspension of coal supplies also includes the so-called 
strategic reserves. 
  On Friday, the Turow brown coal mine in Turoszow suspended 
coal supplies for the local Turow power station. The strike 
committee at the mine told a PAP journalist that output of its 
power units would gradually decrease during the day. 

</TEXT>

