<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly Chairman Leaves for Brussels </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Assembly Chairman Leaves for Brussels </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804153394 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1100 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2804153394 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Croatian Assembly Chairman Stipe Mesic left for 
Brussels this morning to attend a two-day working conference of 
international parliamentarians which will discuss justice and 
progress as bases for peace in Bosnia-Herzegovina. Prior to his 
departure for Brussels to attend the conference, which is to be 
held under the sponsorship of Egon Alfred Klepsch, chairman of 
the European Parliament, Mesic said he will present to the 
conference a Croatian proposal that the international community 
return to its principle of the inviolability of borders. This 
principle will secure an undivided Bosnia-Herzegovina, while the 
occupied areas in Croatia will be fully reintegrated into its 
legal and constitutional system. Bosnia-Herzegovina should be 
demilitarized, and also Serbia, which presents the worst danger 
for this part of the world. President Mesic also said he will 
meet parliamentarians from a number of countries in the course 
of his visit to Brussels. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

