<H3> <TI>   Transportation Agreement Signed With Iran </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Transportation Agreement Signed With Iran </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2804161094 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1500 
GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2804161094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The ninth session of the Intergovernmental 
Bulgarian-Iranian Commission on Technical and Economic 
Cooperation has ended with the signing of specific agreements. 
The leaders of the two delegations -- Transportation Minister 
Ermenkov on the Bulgarian side and 'Ali Akbar Torkan, Iranian 
minister of roads and transportation -- signed a memorandum and 
agreement on air communications which will serve as a legal 
basis for opening regular air routes between Sofia and Iran. 
The two ministers also initialed an agreement on alleviating 
double taxation. 

</TEXT>

