<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Next Finance Minister Stresses Curbing Inflation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Next Finance Minister Stresses Curbing Inflation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY3003232194 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 
2200 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY3003232194 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Renata Verissimo from Brasilia] </F>
  [Text] Future Finance Minister Rubens Ricupero will be 
sworn in on 5 April. He said today he will not touch the 
government economic plan. 
  Ricupero will spend the next four days in Brasilia, talking 
with the economic team to learn about issues at his new 
ministry. He admitted he is not well acquainted with all issues 
and that it would be premature to comment on any decision he 
might make. Ricupero confirmed that he intends to maintain the 
entire current economic team but he also is bringing along five 
advisers to help him in his new post. He also promised he will 
not modify the government economic plan. He said he totally 
favors the economic plan, and that he believes in the FHC 
[Fernando Henrique Cardoso] plan's success. Ricupero also chose 
the fight against inflation as his No. 1 goal: 
  [Begin Ricupero recording] I consider inflation the first 
problem that must be solved because without stability, there is 
no solution. Without stability, no commerce, or regional system, 
or industrial policy, or anything else will work. Therefore, 
that is the main subject of my convictions. As for the details 
and how inflation will be curbed, evidently it depends on the 
daily analysis of the economy's performance. [end recording] 
  Minister Ricupero added that President Itamar Franco is 
analyzing some names to replace him in the Environment Ministry. 
According to Ricupero, some of the possible candidates are 
former Ibama [Brazilian Institute for the Environment and 
Renewable Natural Resources] President Fernando Cesar Mesquita 
and Amazon Secretary Henrique Brandao Cavalcanti. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

