Daily Report 
<DATE1>  30 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Forces Seize 1,051 Kg Cocaine Paste </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Forces Seize 1,051 Kg Cocaine Paste </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY3003124194 Madrid EFE in Spanish 0047 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY3003124194 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lima, 29 Mar (EFE) -- Today, General Nicolas 
Hermoza, chief of the High Command of the Peruvian Armed Forces, 
reported that the price of cocaine base has fallen abruptly 
following recent security service actions against the 
trafficking gangs. Hermoza said the price of washed cocaine base 
has fallen the past few weeks from $1,500 to $150 per kilo. He 
presented 23 traffickers to the media, who were captured in the 
jungle department of Madre de Dios while shipping 1,051 kg of 
cocaine to Colombia. Hermoza also showed assets seized from the 
traffickers, including electric generators, precursors to 
manufacture cocaine base, communications equipment, and vehicles. 
  The traffickers were captured in several operations last 
week 
in the province of Inapari, Madre de Dios Department, on the 
Brazilian borde, where a drug collection center operated. 
Hermoza indicated that the cocaine paste, which was to have been 
processed into cocaine hydrochloride in Colombia, had arrived 
from the Huallaga valleys and from the Ucayali River area. 
  The military commander said: "These traffickers' capture and 
their equipment is proof that land and air actions in the 
Huallaga and Ucayali areas have caused the trafficking axis to 
be moved from there to Madre de Dios Department." 
  Security forces seized 3,653 kg of basic paste and captured 
13 traffickers on 24 February in Boca Manu, also in Madre de 
Dios Department, in the largest drug seizure ever in this Andean 
country. Peru produces some 2,000 tons of basic paste per annum, 
which is exported mainly to Colombia where the Cali and Medellin 
"cartels" process it into the pure cocaine that is sold in the 
United States and Europe. Two-thirds of all cocaine consumed in 
the world is processed from the basic paste that comes from Peru. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

