<H3> <TI>   PCN To Support ARENA in Runoff </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PCN To Support ARENA in Runoff </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA3103032094 San Salvador EL DIARIO DE HOY in Spanish 25 Mar 
94 p 85 </F>

<F P=103> PA3103032094 </F>
<F P=104>  San Salvador EL DIARIO DE HOY </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In one of the first expressions of support in light 
of the upcoming second round of elections, the presidential 
candidate for the National Conciliation Party [PCN] that, 
according to the vote count, came in fourth in the first round 
of elections, has said that his party will support the 
Nationalist Republican Alliance [ARENA]. 
  Colonel Roberto Escobar Garcia, a lawyer and PCN secretary 
general, said yesterday that his party will support ARENA in the 
runoff. Even though the Supreme Electoral Tribunal has not made 
an official announcement, there are indications that it will be 
held on 24 April. 
  According to political observers, ARENA should not pursue an 
alliance in confronting the left in the runoff because it has 
enough strength to defeat all the leftist parties combined. They 
also believe Fidel Chavez Mena does not have the leadership to 
call on the rank and file to vote for ARENA. 

</TEXT>

