<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Four People Injured in Lima Bomb Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Four People Injured in Lima Bomb Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY3003132494 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1156 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY3003132494 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lima, 30 Mar (EFE) -- Four people were injured 
today, two seriously, in downtown Lima during a bomb attack by 
the Maoist Shining Path gang against an Entelperu [National 
Telecommunications Enterprise of Peru] office that was yet to be 
inaugurated. 
  Sources at the hospital where the victims were treated said 
the bomb injured two peddlers, one of whom lost an arm, who were 
sleeping on the street near the targeted office. The other two 
victims were an Entelperu guard and a pedestrian who lost an 
eye. The bomb was in a black bag that had been planted by two 
women. 
  On the night of 28 March, Shining Path members planted 
explosives at four banks, three offices of the Telefonica 
company, and two Entelperu offices, the latter two companies 
were recently purchased by the Spanish Telefonica Internacional 
company for $2.002 billion. Shining Path terrorists also 
attacked a Navy facility and knocked down three power pylons in 
a Lima district causing some short, sporadic blackouts in the 
city. 

</TEXT>

