<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   MIR Molotov Cocktail Attack Injures 9 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MIR Molotov Cocktail Attack Injures 9 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA3103224894 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1930 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA3103224894 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Leon (Mexico), 31 Mar (EFE) -- Today, authorities 
reported that nine people were injured during a Molotov cocktail 
attack allegedly executed by members of the Leftist 
Revolutionary Movement (MIR) [Movimiento de Izquierda 
Revolucionaria] in Leon, Guanajuato, central Mexico. The attack, 
which occurred yesterday afternoon, has left more than 50 people 
homeless because it started a fire that destroyed 13 houses. 
  Local police reported the reasons for the incident are still 
undetermined, but witnesses say two men called Arturo Andrade 
and Rito Duran, MIR leaders, were the ones who threw the bombs. 
Area residents said this is not the first time the alleged 
culprits have attacked the area with explosives. Five years ago, 
the residents say, those people also threw bombs at them because 
they refused to pay a cooperation quota to their organization. 
The attack was apparently aimed against the house of Maria 
Guadalupe Perez, a former MIR member who decided to leave that 
organization a few months ago. MIR is an ultra-left political 
organization that emerged in the past decade and has influence 
in several states in central Mexico. MIR has not openly declared 
itself an armed group. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

