<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Chile monitored through 31 
March. 
  The National Petroleum Enterprise decided to increase oil 
and 
kerosene prices. As of 26 March, 81-93 octane gasoline increases 
4 pesos per liter and kerosene drops 2 pesos per liter. 
(Santiago Radio Cooperativa Network in Spanish 2300 GMT 25 Mar 
94) 
  CCU, United Breweries Company, purchased 15.24 percent of 
the 
Croatian company Karlovacka Pivovara. CCU's partner, Southern 
Breweries Establishments, purchased 15.24 percent of the 
Croatian company. CCU and Southern Breweries Establishments 
purchased 151,126 common registered shares of Karlovacka 
Pivovara for 10.7 million German marks, equivalent to 
$6,342,620. (Santiago ESTRATEGIA in Spanish 18 Mar 94 p 13) 

