<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Electoral Developments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Electoral Developments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA3103194294 </F>
<F P=103> PA3103194294 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on developments related to the Colombian elections 
scheduled for 22 May 1994. 
  While campaigning in Giron, Santander Department, 
Conservative Party presidential candidate Andres Pastrana 
pledged to strengthen Colombia's industrial sector and to 
eliminate contraband. Pastrana said: "The country must wage a 
frontal assault on contraband to prevent it from plunging 
thousands of people into poverty and unemployment, as is now 
happening in Colombia." (Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision 
Television Cadena 1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 26 Mar 94) 
  Ernesto Samper now is the sole leader of the Liberal Party, 
which he is reorganizing. He is forming a broad-based party 
that will include all sectors. Carlos Lleras de la Fuente, 
Rodolfo Gonzalez and David Turbay, former presidential hopefuls 
who vied for the party's nomination, will be Samper's direct 
advisers. (Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 in 
Spanish 1730 GMT 25 Mar 94) 

</TEXT>

