<H3> <TI>   Optimistic About Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Optimistic About Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL3103221894 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL3103221894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina trusts in the 
success of the April conference, which will bring together 
representatives of the Cuban Government and a portion of the 
Cuban community abroad. Robaina announced that so far, the 
majority of invitations for The Nation and the Emigre Community 
Conference have been accepted. Robaina reiterated that 
extremists (la histeria) are not invited to this meeting. 
Robaina added that the meetings will focus on immigration, the 
parliamentary system, family reunification, and travel 
procedures, but that the Cuban organizers are open to including 
other subjects. 
  [Radio Rebelde adds later in the cast that at Robaina's 
invitation and in his company, members of the diplomatic corps 
are visiting the Isle of Youth Municipality] 

</TEXT>

