<H3> <TI>   Minag Delegate Discusses Worker Redistribution </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minag Delegate Discusses Worker Redistribution </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL3103233494 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1000 
GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL3103233494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Since 1990, the Ministry of Agriculture [Minag] has 
relocated approximately 5,000 workers to production and service 
positions in Matanzas. That attitude has allowed 70 percent of 
workers to be directly involved in the production of goods and 
for the rest to be employed in technical, administrative, and 
management positions. 
  Noel Lopez, a Minag delegate in Matanzas, stated that with 
the creation of 41 Basic Cooperative Production Units [UBPC's], 
work relations have improved even more. He stated that even 
though UBPC's have not been created in the pork, fish, and 
citrus branches, organizational measures have increased the 
number of workers who directly participate in production. He 
stated that in Matanzas' citrus sector, 83 percent of the more 
than 600 excess workers from various sectors are now directly 
employed in agricultural tasks. 

</TEXT>

