<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Havana Radio Reports Suspension </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Havana Radio Reports Suspension </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0104183794 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1000 
GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0104183794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As a noble tribute to the Cuban people, the upcoming 
May Day will be turned into a decisive boost to production tasks 
like the sugarcane, tuber, and vegetable harvests and the 
planting and weeding. Pedro Ross Leal, secretary general of the 
Cuban Workers Federation, stated in Havana that the traditional 
Revolution Square rally and parade will not be held this May 
Day. Ross added that the occasion will be observed by means of 
ceremonies in the provinces and workplaces in keeping with the 
characteristics and resources of the different individual 
regions. These ceremonies will be held on 30 April because a 
special session of the National Assembly of the People's 
Government is scheduled for 1 May. Ross added that this is the 
result of a desire to keep May Day alive, as well as keeping 
alive, above all, the spirit of the workers assemblies recently 
held thoroughout Cuba and described by Fidel as a tremendous 
process by Cuba's union movement. 
  Ross stressed that one can pay no greater homage to Cuba's 
workers than to discuss, on May Day, their suggestions on how to 
streamline the nation's finances, since the workers will be 
responsible for implementing the economic measures to be adopted 
in Cuba. 

</TEXT>

