<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Electric Union Reports Breakdowns, Outages </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Electric Union Reports Breakdowns, Outages </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0104213194 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0104213194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 1 April, the Electrical Union issued the 
following communique on the breakdowns and other situations 
affecting the output of electric plants: 
  As reported, since last week, outages have exceeded the 
national schedule of outages due to breakdowns of generator 
units at several electrical plants. This lessens the electricity 
generation capacity of the National Electric System. The Diez de 
Octubre plant, in Nuevitas, experienced a temporary fuel 
shortage that forced it to reduce its output between 26 and 31 
March; this situation was resolved last night. 
  The Electrical Union reported that the situation will 
continue over the next few days, including 2 and 3 April. The 
outages will continue to be longer than scheduled and in 
accordance with the outage program designed in each region to 
cover this period. Maintenance workers at the power plants are 
working around the clock to complete repairs and increase the 
output of the National Electric System in the shortest time 
possible. 

</TEXT>

