  [Text] Death squads are being blamed for the murder of 
Guatemalan Constitutionality Court President Epaminondas 
Gonzalez in Guatemala City on the night of 1 April. According to 
Magistrate Edmundo Vasquez Martinez, paramilitary groups in 
Guatemala have not been dismantled, and assassinations and 
actions against peace and security continue. 
  Meanwhile, it has been reported that Air Force planes are 
overflying Guatemala City, heavily armed soldiers have cordoned 
off the city, and Constitutionality Court magistrates are 
discussing the situation. 

