<H3> <TI>   Zambian Foreign Minister Signs Accords </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zambian Foreign Minister Signs Accords </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0204172994 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1510 GMT 
2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0204172994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 2 April, Zambian Foreign Minister Remmy Kaindu 
Gilly Mushota leaves for Jamaica to continue a tour of the 
Caribbean. During his busy one-week official visit, which 
strengthened cooperation between Zambia and Cuba, the Zambian 
official discussed details of Zambian President Frederick 
Chiluba's forthcoming trip to Cuba. 
  Mushota met with high-level Cuban officials and visited the 
Genetic Engineering and Biotechnology Center, the Finlay 
Institute, and Santiago de Cuba Province. He also met with Raul 
Trujillo, first vice minister of the Ministry of the Sugar 
Industry, a meeting which paved the way for a technical 
assistance agreement. Mushota also held a news conference during 
which he stated that his visit to Cuba has been extremely 
positive and that he is very pleased with the agreements 
concerning health, sports, and sugarcane agriculture that have 
been signed. 

</TEXT>

