<H3> <TI>   Sports Agreements Signed With Ecuador, Spain </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sports Agreements Signed With Ecuador, Spain </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0204032094 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 0100 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0204032094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two sports agreements were signed this afternoon 
with Ecuador and Spain respectively at the headquarters of the 
National Institute for Sports, Physical Education, and 
Recreation [INDER]. (Sabino Hernandez), president of the 
Ecuadoran Sports Committee, together with Conrado Martinez 
Corona and Manuel Gonzalez Guerra, signed the Cuba-Ecuador 
exchange document for the period of 1994-95. The agreement 
establishes increasing Cuban technicians in Ecuador in the 
upcoming months to reach a total of 70 as well as reciprocal 
participation of the two countries in events of diverse 
disciplines. 
  On the other hand, (Francisco Guzon), deputy chief of the 
Spanish Superior Sports Council, and INDER Vice President Raul 
Villanueva signed a similar cooperation agreement for the 
current year, described by the visitor as one of the most 
important agreements signed by his country. The agreement 
includes 30 points of exchange in various spheres, including the 
participation of athletes in reciprocal tournaments. 

</TEXT>

