<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Arrest 3 More Persons in Colosio Case </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Arrest 3 More Persons in Colosio Case </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0104173494 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 1653 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0104173494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 1 Apr (DPA) -- Three other persons 
suspected of participating in the assassination of Luis Donaldo 
Colosio, Institutional Revolutionary Party [PRI] candidate for 
president, have been arrested in Tijuana. 
  According to the radio station Radio Red, three or four 
persons involved in Colosio's assassination were taken from 
Tijuana to Mexico City in deep secrecy. The radio station says 
that everything indicates the persons are Vicente Mayoral 
Valenzuela and his son Rodolfo Mayoral, security agents during 
Colosio's visit to Lomas Taurinas, a Tijuana neighborhood, and 
witnesses to his death. Another person reportedly is Rodolfo 
Rivapalacio, coordinator of Colosio's security in Tijuana, who 
hired members of the group known as Tucan for security tasks. 
The station went on to say that the group includes a fourth 
person, whom the station has not yet identified. 
  Mario Aburto Martinez, a 23-year-old mechanic, and former 
policeman Tranquilino Sanchez Vanegas, 57, accused of having 
assisted the killer, are officially being held at the Almoloya 
de Juarez Maximum Security Prison. In addition, the Mexico City 
press today mentioned the possibility of the murder being 
ordered by drug traffickers, who intended to divert public 
attention. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

