<H3> <TI>   Commission Created To Aid Investigation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commission Created To Aid Investigation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0304034694 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0430 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0304034694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Baja California State Congress has created a 
special commission to help investigate the assassination of Luis 
Donaldo Colosio Murrieta, former PRI [Institutional 
Revolutionary Party] presidential candidate. The commission 
will continue to gather any new evidence Baja California 
residents may present and send it to the attorney general of the 
republic. Francisco Javier Reynoso Nino, Baja California 
Congress secretary, has made this announcement in Mexicali. 
  [Begin Reynoso recording] We have started direct relations 
with the two chambers of Congress, the chambers of deputies and 
senators. Those contacts will, of course, be in both directions 
and directed to further the investigations. We know, of course, 
Congress is not an office to investigate crimes, but we will be 
attentive to any information that becomes available and we will 
immediately report it to the corresponding authorities. [end 
recording] 
  Reynoso also said that although the Baja California State 
Congress is not an investigative office, it can volunteer 
available information to further the Special Prosecutor's 
Office's investigation of the criminal case. He added the Baja 
California Congress is demanding Colosio's murder be clarified 
to the satisfaction of all the people. 

</TEXT>

