<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Text" of Bulletin No. 1 issued by the Special Deputy </F>
Attorney General's Office conducting the investigation of the 
murder of Luis Donaldo Colosio, presidential candidate for the 
Mexican Institutional Revolutionary Party, in Mexico City on 31 
March; from the "24 Hours" newscast] 
  [Text] This office believes it has made progress on 
essential aspects of the case. Given the nature of the 
investigation and taking into consideration Special Deputy 
Attorney General Miguel Montes Garcia's commitment to handle the 
information in such a way that the investigation will not be 
hampered or impeded, it has been regarded as advisable to 
withhold the information and release a report in a few days 
after all the important aspects of the investigation have been 
looked at. The work, which is being carried out in accordance 
with the outline of police analysis, comparison, and 
intelligence programs, has yielded positive results. 

</TEXT>

