<F P=106> [From the "Early Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] During his visit to Agualeguas, Nuevo Leon, 
President Carlos Salinas de Gortari sent a message of unity and 
harmony to all Mexicans. In reference to Jose Cordoba Montoya, 
the president indicated that he is a Mexican citizen who works 
with devotion and his experience will help spur on the IDB 
[Inter-American Development Bank], an institution that is of 
interest to Latin America. 
  Later, President Salinas was asked his opinion on the 
appointment of the new PRI [Institutional Revolutionary Party] 
