worked loyally. I am very fond of him and value his services, 
experience, and capability as related to economic issues. I am 
quite sure these attributes will allow him to contribute 
positively to an institution such as the IDB which is very 
important to Latin America's economic and financial interests. 
  [Reporter] Is there any advice you could give him? 
  [Salinas] [words indistinct] 
  [Reporter] Are there any recommendations you could make to 
Mr. Montoya now that he is about to embark on another duty? 
  [Salinas] Only one. I can only recommend that he use his 
great capabilities and experience in [words indistinct]. 
  [Reporter] Mr. President, does the mourning for Mr. 
Colosio's 
death continue? 
  [Salinas] Friday was declared a day of national mourning as 
a 
result of his death.... 
  [Reporter, interrupting] Is this why you have to return? 
  [Salinas] Most of all because of fondness for a lost friend. 
  [Reporter] Mr. President, what can you say about the 
country's current situation? 
  [Salinas] I repeat, my message is one of unity, 
encouragement, and harmony. [end recording] 
  Later on, President Salinas was asked about the nomination 
of 
the new PRI presidential candidate to which he pointed out that 
during 1993 Mr. Zedillo had been one of the leading contenders 
and that he is an intelligent person committed to democracy and 
the legal order. The president added that Mr. Zedillo will be an 
element of unity and harmony. 

</TEXT>

